# Cloudflare Pages _redirects
#
# NOTE: Cloudflare Pages _redirects matches by PATH only — it cannot match on
# hostname. A catch-all like `/*  https://imagespell.com/:splat  301` would also
# fire on imagespell.com itself (same Pages project) and cause an infinite loop.
#
# Therefore the pixelate-tool.pages.dev -> imagespell.com canonical redirect is
# configured as a dashboard **Redirect Rule** (Rules > Redirect Rules) scoped to
#   Hostname equals pixelate-tool.pages.dev
# and NOT here. See README "独自ドメイン接続" for the exact steps.
#
# Path-level redirects (same host) can safely go below this line if ever needed.
